history.content:
SUSA Social Night: Monday, September 7th @ 6:30-8:30 PM PDT

Join the Statistics Undergraduate Student Association and various Statistics faculty and staff (including Head Undergraduate Faculty Advisor Prof. Will Fithian, new Prof. Andrew Bray, and staff advisors Natalie Poulos and Denise Yee) for a night to meet new people and build our community. The event will primarily use gather.town to communicate with each other, and will be hosting games such as jackbox.tv on the Discord server.

Although SUSA will have a short presentation at 6:50pm about the goals of the organization and ways you can get involved, you are welcome to JOIN US HERE anytime between 6:30pm-8:30pm PDT TODAY, 9/7: https://gather.town/vlA1InNh9S786jAa/susa-social-night (the password will be removed when the event starts).

SUSA Facebook page: https://www.facebook.com/susa.berkeley/

SUSA Website: https://susa-ucb.github.io/
